  "legacyPath": "/blog/2012/04/week-15",
  "legacyFile": "blog__2012__04__week-15.html",
  "imageCount": 4,
  "body": "<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1601018424986-5NHTPHF0RP87DUHZPFW8/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n<p>Now it is getting <em>really</em> fun. Not only am I still loving every bit - from the collecting of the week's goodies to documenting all the bits, but what I am most <strong>loving</strong>now is flipping through the entire album. This baby's getting thick.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1601018434176-YY4EJD57T1EJPQEI7XCE/18b-dsc_1386.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I was pretty excited to be home all week. No travels, but plenty of work. I attempted the Paleo diet with my cousin, but failed miserably as I cannot live without cheese. And bacon. And plenty of things that you are not to eat while on this diet. I think I lasted an entire 2 meals and then I cheated (McDonalds in a crunch!), and then I was over it. However, I am trying to make healthier choices and exercise more. Mainly because I don't want to and cannot actually \"diet\". I am enjoying fresh smoothies every morning and trying to incorporate more and more vegetables each day. In fact, this week I may have had kale 5 out of 7 days. Oh and I have been trying to run more. The sun shines longer and there are no excuses after work. Even if I just go 1.5 miles, it is better than nothing.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1601018450568-RQRW2LI44IDTP37VJYGM/18c-dsc_13871.jpg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1601018464680-C48OW9W4C2KLPQ6XOPP6/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p><a href=\"http://annmarielovespaper.wordpress.com/\">Ann-Marie</a> and I worked a lovely Bat Mitzvah at the Annenberg on Saturday night - we were not <em>actually</em> on the cover of InStyle, in case you were wondering.</p><p>Supplies: <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/american-crafts/126959-woodgrain-amy-tangerine-sketchbook-muse-printed-chipboard-thickers-stickers/%3Ffilters%3D_amy%2Btangerine_\">wood Thickers</a>, <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/american-crafts/126958-taffy-amy-tangerine-sketchbook-scene-glitter-foam-thickers-stickers/%3Ffilters%3D_sketchbook%2Bthickers_%252Fstickers\">glitter Thickers</a>, this <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/love-my-tapes/128113-teal-white-diagonal-stripe-washi-tape/%3Ffilters%3D_washi%2Btape_\">striped washi tape</a>, <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/american-crafts/126952-amy-tangerine-sketchbook-6x6-paper-pad/%3Ffilters%3D_sketchbook%2B6x6_%252Fpaper-kits-and-pads\">Sketchbook 6X6 paper pad</a>, <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/_studio%2520calico%2520wood_/wood/\">Studio Calico wood veneer</a>, mostly from <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/last-30-days/\">Two Peas in A Bucket</a>, some from the local independent stores I visited recently. You can see all my Project Life posts <a href=\"http://static.squarespace.com/static/54763a73e4b0d25603e00ba7/54a756aae4b0f2d6f3befd4e/54a773bfe4b0f2d6f3c1cc6d/1420260287567/project-life?format=original\">here</a>. How are all of you doing with Project Life? I was thinking about doing a Q&amp;A post on Project Life and going more in depth on my process if you were interested in hearing my approach. Any questions?</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
